HEADWORD: Burghmaster
<hw>Burgh"mas`ter</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
burgomaster.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mining)</fld> <def>An officer who directs and lays
out the meres or boundaries for the workmen; -- called also
<altname>bailiff</altname>, and <altname>barmaster</altname>.</def>
<mark>[Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Burghmote</ent>⟦br⟧
